The role of computer hardware and operating systems in IT support
Computer hardware and operating systems are the backbone of IT, and both play a key role in IT support. Hardware is the physical components of a computer such as the processor, memory, hard drive, and network devices.
IT support deals with troubleshooting this equipment to keep systems running properly. IT support will aslo handle hardware upgrades when needed. Together, hardware and operating systems create the foundation for all IT 
systems.
